metadata.name: Mandatory Destiny #46
metadata.description:
"Mandatory Destiny" is the fifth collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

It is impossible for everyone to be equal. Too much of a person is defined by random chance. The country they were born in, the financial situation of their family, even their genetics. If someone was unlucky and has low natural IQ, they can't change it. And it affects their life significantly. If someone was born in a poor country or family, it might be extremely harder to get a good education, and later, a well-paying job. Some people are fortunate enough to get a headstart, while others aren't so lucky.

The only way for everyone to be truly equal would be identical starting conditions, and that's utterly impossible to achieve.

metadata.name: Moonlight Impression #102
metadata.description:
I always love to feel the moonlight falling on the mountains and flowing clouds. There is always a scenery in deep inside, it is the kind of picture that you might think of when you are  alone in the deep night. In my case, that's somewhere there's a yellow moon.

This piece presents the combination of the yellow moon with different elements such as mountains, forests and clouds in some transformations.

Many dots of different sizes and colors are used to paint the picture, trying to replicate the texture of a glue painting.

Made with p5js.


Variables:
- 27 sky color schemas
- 27 mountain color schemas

Control(in live view):
- Press [s] to save a high-res png image

metadata.name: Mur #148
metadata.description:
Mur is a series of computational drawings of stacked and falling bricks. The bricks are placed in different configurations of walls, towers, stacks and paths, and are then exposed to gravity. 

The graphics are coded with p5.js and the rigid body simulations with ammo.js. In live mode, press 's' to save a screenshot and 'e' to save a high resolution image. Press 't' to toggle textures. 

Each scene is drawn twice, first brick by brick as they fall or stay in place, then the scene as a whole. Mur is optimized for Chrome, uses WebGL and may not work in all browsers.

metadata.name: Syzers #241
metadata.description:
Syzers is a generative synthesizer project with sounds altered by Tone JS.

···· On Tuesday, May 17, unsold editions will be burned ····

Visually it consists of 16 layers, in which more than 350 elements are combined randomly, generating synthesizers with unique environments and landscapes.
As for the sound, 40 tracks were recorded with analog synthesizers that were then assigned to each of the modules. These, combined in groups of 4, provide thousands of possible combinations. 
In addition, these sounds will be further modified by code effects that will randomly vary their properties.

Click to listen to the sounds

Many thanks to @Jpupper and @Fipiaggio for help with programming the sound part and @Purespider for the template. 
"FXHASH PFP Token Generator" https://github.com/PureSpider/fxhash-pfp

for best resolution "open live" then use the "download image" button on the lower right corner ;)

metadata.name: Tangled #64
metadata.description:
"Tangled" is a generative art project that explores the emergent behaviour of simple shapes moving according to a random flow field. While the final result is always constrained to the shape of a circle, the variation within is endless.

Instructions:
Press "p" to pause the animation.
In live mode, press 1 through 5 to save a PNG version of the final result. The following resolutions are available:
1: 400 x 400 (ideal for Twitter PFP)
2: 1000 x 1000
3: 2000 x 2000
4: 4000 x 4000
5: 5000 x 5000
Please be patient, generating the PNG may take some time!

Made with p5.js.

metadata.name: Chop Chop #32
metadata.description:
Chop Chop is a complementary collection to Caterpillars that I prepared to thank my collectors for the amazing love and interest you showed to my work. I did not want to force my way to your wallets with unsolicited thank-you nfts, so all holders of Caterpillars will have a reserve spot to mint at least 1 tokens per wallet for 0 tez ( I dont understand the reserve options fully, sorry - 128 editions reserved for holders of Caterpillars) . 

The holders of this collection will have reserve spots for my next  collection. The reserve spots will be held for one week from minting, and I prefer the unreserved editions to be fair game for anyone, so first come, first served.

I decided to re-work this older project of mine because it was going to take some time for me to prepare an independent and novel collection and also wanted to continue learning new things. The concept is Paul Klee meets Vector Math and Flow Fields, as you can see the visuals are heavily inspired by Paul Klee's work :)

Under the hood, the circles and triangles act as repulsive forces that break and distort the grid, and push the squares in their range out of their way, forming some holes in the fabric created by the same algo that made Caterpillars. 

I have only added one rarity feature which is the palette because this one uses almost all the palettes from Caterpillars (minus neon dreams). I am hoping that this project will not be about rarity, but more like a thank-you gift and an easy way to access my future work.

Well, I hope you will like it...

- Press "s" to save a png.

- Also, 33% royalty split wth the Processing Foundation, % 33 with the minters (if there will be any secondary sales) 

DISCLAIMER :
I am very very new to coding and not very good at this. I have tried to clean up the code as best as I could, and I hope that there is nothing terribly wrong left inside.

metadata.name: Circles Within Circles Spinning #116
Dithered Gradients #21
metadata.description:
Each Dithered Gradient is generated from an algorithm derived from Pixel Blobs II. Pixels are initially placed onto a canvas in 4 orderly patterns. Every color grows in a deterministic pattern randomly generated before the canvas initializes. Interesting dither patterns are created when 2 colors collide.

Features:
- Saturation: (None=75%, +25%=18.75%, -25%=6.25%)
- Inverted Colors: (true=75%, false=25%)
- Pattern: (Horizontal=75%, Vertical=22.5%, X=1.875%, Box=.625%)

Co-released in partnership with fauxjebus May 10, 2022

metadata.name: contrapuntos #351
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodríguez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.
